
'''= A collaborative forecasting game designed to bring together networks and voices from all over the world to create insights for change.'''

URL = http://game.connected-citizens.org/about

=Description=

"Connected Citizens  described itself as "a global conversation about how connectedness will change the relationship between citizens and governments, and how government services will be designed and delivered in the future". Using a "Foresight Engine", players exchanged ideas "about the opportunites and dilemmas generated in this new world of connected citizenship".

It was initiated by designers & developers and encouraged people to participate through an online platform. Connected Citizens was global in orientation and concerned with democracy, politics & representation; participation; public services; and neighbourhood & community.

It was launched in 22 January 2013 and ended on 23 January 2013."
(http://www.open.edu/openlearn/society/politics-policy-people/participation-now/connected-citizens)


